"$L1d\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",null,{}],[[\"$\",\"$L8\",null,{\"gtmId\":\"GTM-PDDLBRK8\"}],[\"$\",\"$L9\",null,{\"id\":\"hs-script-loader\",\"strategy\":\"lazyOnload\",\"src\":\"//js.hs-scripts.com/46163002.js\"}]],[\"$\",\"$La\",null,{}]]}]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"1e:I[4754,[\"4754\",\"static/chunks/4754-8aab191705aa8914.js\",\"8710\",\"static/chunks/8710-cc4bbfe7e72eb54f.js\",\"7934\",\"static/chunks/7934-0cec3d18aac18c43.js\",\"3306\",\"static/chunks/3306-908f080a9a1cc778.js\",\"9662\",\"static/chunks/9662-a9aa1fbb00165833.js\",\"867\",\"static/chunks/app/%5Blocale%5D/whitepaper/page-1cc5a2888bf223de.js\"],\"default\"]\n1f:Tc32,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cList\u003e\u003cListItem\u003e\u003cHeading\u003eDongdaemun Design Plaza\u003c/Heading\u003e This major urban landmark in Seoul, designed by Zaha Hadid and Samoo, is renowned for its neofuturistic architecture. As the centerpiece of South Korea's fashion hub, DDP features a walkable park on its roofs, large global exhibition spaces, futuristic retail stores, and restored sections of the Seoul fortress. It also hosts regular fashion shows, exhibitions, and cultural events, making it a vibrant destination for visitors.\u003c/ListItem\u003e\u003cListItem\u003e\u003cHeading\u003eNamsangol Hanok Village\u003c/Heading\u003e Step back in time at Namsangol Hanok Village, an ancient village from the Joseon period (1392-1910), located on the northern side of Namsan Mountain. Opened to the public in 1998, this village offers free admission and features traditional Korean houses (Hanoks), cultural experiences like trying on Hanbok (traditional Korean clothing), and traditional tea ceremonies. It's also a picturesque spot for photography.\u003c/ListItem\u003e\u003cListItem\u003e\u003cHeading\u003eBukchon Hanok Village\u003c/Heading\u003e Preserved in the heart of modern Seoul, Bukchon Hanok Village offers a unique glimpse into Korea’s past with its well-preserved Hanoks. Walking through the alleyways lined with these historic homes feels like time travel. The village is conveniently situated between Gyeongbokgung Palace, Changdeokgung Palace, and Jongmyo Shrine, making it an excellent stop for those interested in Korean history and culture.\u003c/ListItem\u003e\u003cListItem\u003e\u003cHeading\u003eSeoul Forest\u003c/Heading\u003e A large park beloved by locals, Seoul Forest is especially popular for its cherry blossoms in Spring and the Ginkgo Tree Forest in Autumn. The park has a rich history, having transitioned from royal hunting grounds to a water treatment facility, horse racing tracks, and now an eco-friendly city park. Visitors can also enjoy a deer park, butterfly conservatory, and various art installations.\u003c/ListItem\u003e\u003cListItem\u003e\u003cHeading\u003eGarosugil\u003c/Heading\u003e Located in Sinsa-dong, Gangnam, Garosugil is a trendy street filled with the hottest Korean and international brands. It’s a favorite shopping destination for both locals and tourists, offering a wide range of unique stores and chic cafes. The area’s popularity also means you might spot celebrities and social media influencers while exploring.\u003c/ListItem\u003e\u003cListItem\u003e\u003cHeading\u003eDosan Park\u003c/Heading\u003e Dosan Park in Seoul has emerged as a center of luxury fashion, where world-renowned brands gather. This peaceful green space is named after the Korean independence activist An Chang-ho (pen name Dosan). The surrounding area has become a hub for luxury fashion lovers, with flagship stores from brands like Song Ji-oh, Woo Young-mi, and street brands like Supreme and Palas.\u003c/ListItem\u003e\u003cListItem\u003e\u003cHeading\u003eSeongsu\u003c/Heading\u003e Often dubbed the “Brooklyn of Seoul,” Seongsu has become a creative hub known for its industrial-chic vibe. The area is famous for its pop-up stores, art spaces, and cafes. Spend a day here, and you’re bound to stumble upon multiple pop-up shops and creative events, making it a must-visit for those looking for something unique and trendy.\u003c/ListItem\u003e\u003c/List\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"1d:[\"$\",\"$L1e\",null,{\"formats\":{\"dateTime\":{\"short\":{\"year\":\"numeric\",\"month\":\"2-digit\",\"day\":\"2-digit\"},\"medium\":{\"year\":\"numeric\",\"month\":\"short\",\"day\":\"2-digit\"},\"long\":{\"day\":\"numeric\",\"month\":\"long\",\"year\":\"numeric\"}},\"number\":{\"compact\":{\"notation\":\"compact\",\"style\":\"decimal\",\"maximumFractionDigits\":1},\"abbreviated\":{\"notation\":\"compact\",\"compactDisplay\":\"short\"}}},\"locale\":\"en\",\"messages\":{\"components\":{\"countdown\":{\"days\":\"Days\",\"hours\":\"Hours\",\"minutes\":\"Minutes\",\"seconds\":\"Seconds\"},\"ecosystemProjectSubmission\":{\"title\":\"Showcase Your Project\",\"description\":\"If you have a project \u003chighlighted\u003ebuilt on Aptos\u003c/highlighted\u003e, we invite you to share it with us.\",\"submitProject\":\"Submit Project\"},\"newsletterSubscriptionDialog\":{\"client\":{\"openDialogButtonTitle\":\"Open newsletter subscription dialog\",\"dialogTitle\":\"Subscribe for Updates\",\"dialogDescription\":\"Periodically receive network news, helpful resources, upcoming events and other offers you might be interested in.\"}}},\"footerNav\":{\"network\":{\"label\":\"Network\",\"title\":\"Aptos Network\"},\"foundation\":{\"label\":\"Foundation\",\"title\":\"Aptos Foundation\"},\"numbers\":{\"label\":\"Network Numbers\",\"title\":\"Aptos Network Numbers\"},\"press\":{\"label\":\"Press\",\"title\":\"What the media is saying about Aptos\"},\"blog\":{\"label\":\"Blog\"},\"brand\":{\"label\":\"Brand\",\"title\":\"Aptos brand assets and guidelines\"},\"careers\":{\"label\":\"Careers\",\"title\":\"Join the Aptos team\"},\"developers\":{\"label\":\"Developers\"},\"docs\":{\"label\":\"Developer Docs\"},\"github\":{\"label\":\"Aptos on Github\"},\"community\":{\"label\":\"Community\"},\"events\":{\"label\":\"Events\"},\"forum\":{